um); and an interview with a young director new to the field (Michael Dowse). Together these players in the Canadian film scene capture the energy, success, and tribulations of a fascinating cultural industry. The Young, the Restless, and the Dead is the first volume in a series of interviews with key cultural creators in the field of cinema. It seeks to bring to a wide audience the insights and emotions, the trials and achievements of significant figures in Canadian film. George Melnyk talks about The Young, the Restless, and the Dead with Eric Volmers of the Calgary Herald. Read the interview online.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCinémaxHistoirexCanada. 0aMotion picture producers and directorsxBiographyxCanada. 0aMotion picture producers and directorsxInterviewsxCanada. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszCanadavBiography. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszCanadavInterviews. 0aMotion picturesxHistoryxCanada. 0aMotion pictureszCanadaxHistory. 0aProducteurs et réalisateurs de cinémaxBiographiesxCanadaxCanada. 0aProducteurs et réalisateurs de cinémaxEntretiensxCanada. 4aFilm & Media. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aMelnyk, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelnyk, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458113940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554581139423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781554581139/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgr